post_text: Parents--please let us know if you would like to have school meals delivered to your house this year. All students in grades K-12 are eligible, regardless of the method of instruction--in person, hybrid, or fully remote. Meals will be delivered for the week on Mondays to your home for the days that your child is learning remotely. If you have returned the form you received from the school, you are all set. If you have not returned the form yet, please do so as soon as possible, or you may call the District Office at 988-5038 to arrrange delivery.

post_text: Congratulations Emily--Great job!!! #SpartanPride!
shared_text:
AAA Northeast
August 22 at 12:30 PM ·

Congratulations to Emily Brandenburg from Unatego Central School District! She was chosen as a School Safety Patroller of the Year thanks to her leadership qualities, safety skills, school involvement, volunteerism and patrol experience.

Here is a quote from her winning essay: “Being a safety patrol captain has taught me more responsibility and to be more organized which will help me as I continue to grow. I had to make sure that I was also following all the rules that we had set for the younger kids, and the rules the school has in place for all of us. At the same time, I had to keep my school grades up. I want to thank my advisors for believing in me and picking me to be a part of this amazing journey.”

Learn more about the AAA School Safety Patrol Program in #YourAAA: https://bit.ly/2Qj3gHr

Parent Survey for fall 2020 at Unatego

We are currently finishing our planning process for the fall semester at Unatego and would like feedback from parents and guardians before we complete our work. We ask that you take a few minutes to complete the survey below to help us with our planning. Be aware that not all options listed below may be available or feasible but we do need to hear from all our families what their preferences would be. Thank you for working with us as we endeavor to create a reopening plan that provides our students with a high-quality learning experience in a safe environment. Here is the link to the survey which will be available through Monday, July 27.

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/Z6QFFQF

Unatego Graduation is tonight at 7:00 pm on the HS Football Field. Due to COVID19 attendance is limited to 150 persons, including graduates, staff, and guests. No one will be admitted without a ticket. We do not want to jeopardize this event for our students so please do not attend if you do not have a ticket. However, the event will be livestreamed for those unable to attend. The link for the livestream is

mussaw.me/live

The "Virtual" graduation video is completed as well and will be available on line immediately following tonight's outdoor ceremony. Check back on our FB page after 8:00 pm for that link.

Congratulations to all our graduates and their families!

. This is a reminder that student pick up of all school materials will take place on Wednesday, June 17th between 9:00-3:00. Students will receive the contents of their lockers and must return all school materials at that time. This includes: Chromebooks, chargers, textbooks, library books and any other school materials. We look forward to seeing you on Wednesday!

This survey was posted last week and we are grateful for the more than 100 parents who responded. But since we would like to hear from as many of you as possible, we have reopened the survey until next Tuesday. If you have already completed it, thank you. If not, please take a moment and answer a few questions so we can better plan for the future.

Here is the link to the short survey: https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/X8LJF3Z

Thank you!

post_text:
Last Day of Instruction

The last day of instruction for this school year will be June 17, unless advised differently by the State Education Department or the Governor. You will be receiving further details from your child’s principal in the coming days.

Thank you all for working so well with the school during the recent unprecedented closure of our buildings. We look forward to reopening our buildings and seeing the students back in the classroom in the fall, if we are allowed and can do so safely.

In the meantime, stay safe and be well.

post_text: For the past 34 years, Mrs. Theresa Finch, retired Unatego Kindergarten teacher, has worked with her class to make a quilt in kindergarten and then she displays it at the High School when they are seniors getting ready to graduate. Since we are closed for the remainder of the school year, it couldn't be displayed but Mrs. Finch created photos so that this year's Class of 2020 could relive their youthful years as they graduate. Here is the quilt and pictures from days gone by. Retirees and those who have passed in the last year are also remembered. From Unatego and the Class of 2020--Thank you Mrs. Finch!

shared_text:
Delaware-Chenango-Madison-Otsego BOCES
May 11 at 10:14 AM ·

Senior profiles for students in the DCMO BOCES Career and Technical education programs continue, giving us even more reasons to be proud. Next up, Alyssa!

Alyssa Feliu (Unatego): Security & Law Enforcement Program at the Harrold Campus

Alyssa plans on attending Suny Broome for Criminal Justice and would like to become a K-9 patrol officer.

She is involved in SkillsUSA and SADD, and she likes reading, being outdoors and Jiu Jitsu.

Alyssa had this to say about attending her CTE program: "I’ve learned a controlled mind set and I believe it’s wonderful that we leave with one certificate that can truly jump start us on a career we truly want to pursue."

Congratulations, Alyssa!

Schools Remain Closed for the rest of the School Year
05/01/2020

Today, Governor Cuomo announced that all public schools in New York State will remain closed for the rest of the 2019-2020 academic year. Distance Learning will continue until sometime in mid-June as will the school lunch/breakfast program. More information will be available next week. Please continue to stay safe, practice social distancing and good hygiene.

shared_text:
Delaware-Chenango-Madison-Otsego BOCES
April 14 at 4:10 PM ·

Despite the public health crisis, schools are finding new ways to celebrate seniors during extended school closures. DCMO is participating too by featuring senior profiles for students in our Career and Technical Education (CTE) programs. First up: Mychaelah Christian!

Mychaelah Christian (Unatego): Visual Communications Program at the Harrold Campus

Mychaelah plans on attending SUNY Delhi to pursue an Associates in Arts Degree in Liberal Arts & Science/General Studies then transferring into Veterinary Science Technology (AAS).

Her hobbies include derbies, dirt track racing, fishing and spending time with friends and family.

She believes the biggest benefit to attending her CTE program has been: "Creativity and constructive criticism while being able to be myself."

Congratulations, Mychaelah!

For the next of our Career and Technical Education Senior Profiles, we are proud to present Colton Hoyle!

Colton Hoyle (Unatego):
Conservation & Heavy Equipment Program at the Harrold Campus

Colton plans on becoming a Department of Environmental Conservation Officer.

His favorite activities: FFA, football, baseball, and farming. "I love to go fishing."

Board of Education Meeting Closed to the Public

March 23, 2020

The Unatego Board of Education meeting scheduled for tonight will still take place. Due to the State of Emergency, members of the public will not be allowed to attend, as public gatherings of ten or more people are currently not allowed, as per Governor Cuomo’s executive order. In fact, several board members and school administrators may also not be there in person but will participate via videoconferencing. This videoconference will be available to members of the public.

There will be a board budget workshop starting at 6:00 pm, followed by the regularly scheduled meeting at 7:00 pm. The physical location of the meeting is the Board Room at the Junior-Senior High School.
Anyone wishing to participate in the Zoom videoconference should go to the following link:
https://zoom.us/j/359527361

You can access the zoom meeting from a PC, MAC, tablet, or smart phone. In some cases you may need to download the zoom app.

Thank you for your understanding and patience during this difficult time.

Unatego Kindergarten Registration

Due to the closing of the Unatego Central School, Kindergarten Registration will be modified. Please e-mail your documents needed (your child’s birth certificate, immunization record, custody papers if applicable, and proof of residency (physical address- no PO Boxes) along with the packet you received to smaruszewski@unatego.stier.org or mail to Unatego Central School, 2641 State Highway 7, PO Box 483, Otego, NY 13825.

It is important that all children be registered for the 2020–2021 kindergarten program. If you have any questions please e-mail Sherry Maruszewski, District Registrar, at the above or call 988-5097.

To be eligible for kindergarten, a child must be at least 5 years old on or before December 1st, 2020. A child who turns six on or before December 1st, 2020 must attend school starting in September 2020.

Mike Snider Principal
Unatego Elementary School

post_text:
Message from Middle School Principal Patti Hoyt.

We want to insure that instruction continues during the closure of the school building.

Teachers are preparing instructional materials for students. Much of it will be available in Google Classroom, so students will be taking their Chromebook and a charger home. We will be providing paper packets for students without reliable internet access.

The Middle School building will be open on Wednesday from 8:00 to 3:30 for students to stop in and pick up any materials they may need. In order to limit the number of people entering the building, we are asking that only students enter the building.

We are encouraging students to bring home their gym clothes so the locker room can be thoroughly cleaned.
If you are not able to come in on Wednesday during the hours provided, please call the school at 988-5097 so we can make other arrangements.
Most of all, we want you to follow all of the health department recommendations to be safe and stay healthy.

post_text:
Message to the Unatego Community

As you know by now, Unatego and other area schools will be closed for a minimum of two weeks, based on a directive from the Otsego County Department of Health, due to an abundance of caution regarding the Novel Corona Virus pandemic. Although there are still no confirmed cases in Otsego County, at this time we will remain closed from March 16 through March 27 or possibly longer. There will be no athletic practices or games during the closure and extracurricular activities are cancelled until further notice. Access to school buildings will be limited. We are working diligently to finish our plan to provide continuity of operations, instruction, and availability of meals and hope to have information out by the end of the day tomorrow. We will be in touch with students, parents, and staff using School Messenger calling, posting on the District Website and the District Facebook page as well as Twitter (DrDaveUnatego)

In the meantime, follow all precautions, be safe, and we will get through this emergency together.

Community Foundation Donates to the Elementary School Safety Patrol Trip to Washington DC!

At the Unatego Elementary Super Spartan Star Assembly on February 27, 2020, three representatives from the Unadilla Community Foundation presented the Unatego Elementary School Safety Patrol with a $5,000 donation to support a Safety Patrol trip to Washington DC and Philadelphia. The 19-member Elementary Safety Patrol will be joining approximately 8-10 other schools for this bus trip in May.

The Safety Patrol Advisors are: Tam Menz, Michele Wilson, and Darlene Wong.
The Community Foundation representatives are: Kellie Renwick, Greg Relic, and Craig VanCott.

On behalf of our students, we are incredibly grateful to the Community Foundation for their generous gift to help support this once in a lifetime opportunity for our kids!

post_text:
School Board Elections and Budget Vote

Petitions are available for individuals interested in being candidates for the Unatego Central School District Board of Education election on May 19, 2020. There are three (3) board vacancies which are for three years each July 1, 2020 – June 30, 2023. The current seats are held by David Clapper, Byron McMichael and Cindy O’Hara.

Interested candidates must be 18 years old, citizens of the United States and residents of the Unatego Central School District for one year before the election. The completed petition must contain at least twenty-five (25) names of qualified voters in the Unatego Central School District.

Petitions are available at the district office or on-line at www.unatego.com Board of Education section. They must be returned to the school district clerk in the district office between the hours of 8:00 a.m. and 3:30 p.m. on days school is in session. The deadline for all petitions is by 5:00 p.m. April 20, 2020.

post_text:
Unatego Science Foundation News!

Dr. Davis presents Superintendent Richards with a check for $8,000 from the Unatego Science Foundation!

Dr. Davis, the President of the Unatego Science Foundation, presented the District a check for $8,000 this week. The foundation, created to provide Unatego with financial resources for students and teachers, has, since its founding in 2008, donated more than $59,000.

The funds have been used to purchase scientific equipment, materials, and supplies; technology; software; curricular materials; and provide fellowships to deserving students from the district. This past year, Foundation funds provided $500 scholarships to four Unatego students.

Unatego sends a big thank you to Dr. Davis and the Foundation for their past and continuing support of our students and the Science program!

post_text:
Bridges to Great Beginnings--Bridges to Great Beginnings will meet on Tuesday January 14th from 9-10:30 am at the elementary school. This class is for ages 2-4.
Bridges to Great Beginnings is an early literature program at Unatego Central School. This program celebrates the introduction and use of literature for children, ages infant through 4 years, as a means of developing great learners. The program has been developed by a group of therapists to include activities which encourage development of gross motor, fine motor and speech/language skills throughout the early years.

For more information, please contact Anita Grays at agrays@unatego.stier.org or Unatego Elementary school 607-369-6200

post_text:
Unatego Student Councils to Hold Special Day for Unatego Senior Citizens

The Unatego Central School's high school and middle school Student Councils invite all senior citizens of the Unatego Central School District to a special "Senior Citizen Day" on Wednesday, December 11th, 2019. The day will begin at 8:30 with socializing in the Board of Education Room with refreshments. Some fun holiday activities and games will take place after this, and then brunch will be served. There will be prizes awarded for the winners of games and a gift raffle will take place throughout the morning. Finally, the day will end with performances by the senior high band and chorus. The day will end at noon.



Reservations are encouraged for the brunch. Please call 988-5098 to make your reservation

post_text:
From the Junior Class

The Class of 2021 will be holding their second annual Craft and Vendor Fair this Friday night from 5-9. We are also having a Cornhole Tournament and a Basket and Dessert Raffle.

There will be over 20 vendors so you can do some great Christmas shopping. You can also take part in the Cornhole Tournament. There are different categories and the top 3 in each category will win cash or prizes!

In addition we will have a wonderful concession stand so you do not even need to worry about going home to make dinner. We will have pulled chicken and pulled pork, chili and vegetarian chili, mac-n-cheese, and walking tacos.

Please come out this Friday night to support the Class of 2021!!!
